<topic class="popup" template="Popup" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="../../../helpproject.xsd">
  <title translate="true">Flipper Inspector Tool</title>
  <body>
    <para styleclass="Popup Heading"><text styleclass="Popup Heading" translate="true">Flipper Inspector Tool</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Popup Heading"><table rowcount="1" colcount="2" style="cell-padding:0px; cell-spacing:0px; border-width:0px; cell-border-width:0px;">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="vertical-align:middle; width:99px;">
          <para styleclass="Popup Heading"><image src="Flipper Inspector.png" align="left" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption"></image></para>
        </td>
        <td style="vertical-align:middle; width:214px;">
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">Opens an empty </text><text styleclass="Program Feature" translate="true">Inspector</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> window. You can then use the </text><text styleclass="Program Feature" translate="true">Visual Object Finder</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> tab to drag a cursor and locate any visible Dolphin object that you wish to inspect.</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">The </text><text styleclass="Program Feature" translate="true">Flipper Inspector</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> is so called because it allows you to &quot;flip&quot; between two possible views of the object being inspected; the </text><text styleclass="Program Feature" translate="true">Published Aspects</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> view and the </text><text styleclass="Program Feature" translate="true">Instance Variables</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> view.</text></para>
  </body>
</topic>
